Classifiers have also been called &quot;count-classifiers&quot; , &quot;individual classifiers&quot;, , and &quot;qualifying classifiers&quot; (; ).↩
Massifiers have also been called &quot;mass-classifiers&quot; , &quot;non-individual classifiers&quot; , and &quot;quantifying classifiers&quot; (; ). The term &quot;massifier&quot; is used in this article to avoid ambiguous usage of the term &quot;measure word&quot;, which is often used in everyday speech to refer to both classifiers and massifiers .↩
